CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 15, 1945, pg. 25, reads: "Double Celebration - Mrs. Rosalie Joyner of 172 Devilliers Street is enjoying a birthday party, and is also celebrating the return of her brother, Pvt. Frederick Young, who has returned after nineteen months of overseas service. Guests present at the party were Mr. and Mrs. James Young, Pvt. and Mrs. Fred Young, John Joyner, Samuel, John and James Young Jr., Sadie Young, Ada Wilson, Mistress June Carol, Seaman I/C Robert Brown, Edward Haggans, Maggie Maxwell and Marion Tisdale. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Guests at party including Mrs. Young, James Young, Mrs. Young, Pvt. Fred Young, John Joyner, Samuel Young, John Young, James Young Jr., Sadie Young, Ada Wilson, June Carol, Seaman I/C Robert Brown, Edward Haggans, Maggie Maxwell and Marion Tisdale posed in Joyner home, 172 Devilliers Street, Hill District
